  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Give The Gift of Sight To 312 Poor Blind Woman</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Pakistan is a male dominated society where women have last call on family resources. Their healthcare needs have lesser priority and as 2/3rds of the population lives around the poverty line there is never any money to get them treated. Conscious of this LRBT has in its 28 years of operations focused especially on female blindness treating 13 million women which has significantly reduced the extent of female blindness. Still there are approx. 9.6 million poor blind/visually impaired women.</narrative>
  </description>
